# Agentic Rules Framework Integration

<!-- SAFETY_PRECAUTION_START -->
**⚠️ CRITICAL TEMPLATE PROTECTION**: This file is a TEMPLATE ONLY. Agents MUST NOT auto-load, auto-read, or auto-process this file under any circumstances. This file is NEVER executed directly.

**VALID USAGE**: Only load this template when explicitly renamed to one of: `AGENTS.md`, `GEMINI.md`, or `CLAUDE.md` AFTER explicit user activation of framework features.

**INVALID USAGE**: Do not load this file automatically, do not reference it in startup processes, do not include it in any automated framework initialization.
<!-- SAFETY_PRECAUTION_END -->

These rules are **active in this session** — apply them as part of your normal behavior, not as background ceremony to acknowledge and skip. Each section is active only if enabled in its `modules/<module>/settings.json`; if a module is disabled, ignore its section.

## Memory — *when `memory_rules.enabled`*

This project has a **file-based memory** at `./memory/` in the project root. This is the framework's store — **use it, not your editor's built-in memory**, so storage and recall always agree on location.

- **Store**: when the user says "remember…", "save this", or shares a durable fact, decision, or convention, write it as a markdown file at
  `./memory/projects/<project-id>/<category>/<YYYYMMDD>_<category>_memory.md`
  (categories: `technical`, `contextual`, `behavioral`, `sessions`, `topics`). Create directories as needed and tell the user the path.
- **Recall**: before answering something prior context would inform, **read `./memory/` first** — `./memory/index.md` if present, then the relevant project/category files.
- Never store secrets or credentials in project memory.

## Knowledge Graph — *when `rag_rules.knowledge_graph.enabled`*

A simple typed graph lives at `./memory/knowledge_graph/` (markdown, no server required).

- When you learn a durable fact **with a relationship** (X depends on Y, X is part of Y, X supersedes Y), append a node and an edge to the markdown KG — `nodes` and `edges` tables, nodes typed `rule | pattern | fact | procedure | gotcha`.
- Before non-trivial work, consult it for relevant prior knowledge.
- If a `kg` MCP server is connected (the user opted to upgrade), use its tools instead and skip the markdown store.

## Context / RAG — *when `rag_rules.enabled`*

Read efficiently: prefer targeted search and `file:line` reads over dumping whole files; ground claims in the source you read.

## Critical thinking — *when `critical_thinking_rules.enabled`*

Challenge vague requirements — ask for the concrete target or metric instead of silently guessing. Admit uncertainty; verify before asserting.

## Detailed procedures

The exact per-module algorithms live in each module's directory — `modules/memory-rules/`, `modules/rag-rules/`, `modules/critical-thinking-rules/` — inside the file matching this one (e.g. `modules/memory-rules/CLAUDE.md`). Read them when you need the precise steps. The optional `.agentic_initialized` marker and `bootstrap.json` are housekeeping, not prerequisites — never let them block acting on the rules above.

